about_the_job:
Our Client's Profile?

Our client is a startup multinational Industrial Internet of Things (IIOT) which has APAC office in Singapore.

What our client is looking for?

5 years of experience in project management/demand analysis/technology development.
Has implementation experience in the forestry/agricultural industry, large-scale IoT projects, smart manufacturing projects, and enterprise digital transformation projects will be highly preferred;
Having experience working with hydraulic sensor solution, AI related experience is preferred.
Familiar with project management or has a PMP certificate is preferred; familiar with the entire process of project management, and master the characteristics of waterfall and agile model.
Accept domestic and overseas business trips.
Excellent English ability and proficient in speaking Bahasa Indonesia.

What will you do as Business Analyst - Water Management?

Responsible for leading the project implementation team to complete project research, development and implementation, system launch and acceptance;
Responsible for the analysis and design of customer business requirements, control of the scope of requirements, and the preparation of core documents;
Responsible for controlling the implementation process, controlling project scope, schedule, quality, risk, cost and project change management;
Responsible for the coordination and mobilization of various resources during the project implementation process, and able to guide the team implementation consultants and development consultants to complete the tasks assigned;
Responsible for the control and management of on-site personnel during project operation and on-site communication with customer senior management;
